column5: Hey everyone, I got out for a couple hours today on lake simcoe and had a blast. I landed and released 7 whitefish and also iced 5 lakers , keeping these two. I got 1/2 the fish on a 1/2&1/2 williams wobbler and the other 1/2 on minnows and a tip up.
Very well done Richy Nice looking lakers
Very nice Where abouts were you?
Thanks guys , I was fishing on the west side in oro
Nice fish!  Hows the ice out that end?
Well done rich   sounds like a nice day out!!  Hope to do aswell when we hit Beaverton next weekend  Thanx for the report/update.  Streamerguy
Lots of ice , a couple small cracks to go over but as of today no problem with a quad
You are a big ol  Oro counrty boy.LOL  Nice fish there Rich.
yeah man , grew up in hawkestone, what about you ?
